    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "<strong>Another Family Advised Concerning a Savings Account</strong>&mdash;Every week you should lay by in some secure place five or ten dollars not to be used up unless in case of sickness. With economy you may place something at interest. With wise management you can save something after paying your debts.<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">4<span class=\"chapterendnote\">Uncopied <span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"Lt 29, 1884\" data-link=\"14054.4620001\">Letter 29, 1884</span>.</span></a></sup>",
